00:00:09.450 --> 00:00:11.360
Hello! Today we'll deal with a common problem:

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:14.250
The scooter doesn't stop well any longer, because the brake pads are worn down! 

00:00:14.250 --> 00:00:17.350
No problem. I'll show you how you can easily change them! 

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:24.270
First of all, I remove these 5 nuts from the rim. 

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:26.010
The brake pads sit here right under the brake drum.

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:35.190
We use a flat head screwdriver

00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:37.420
to remove the dust cover.

00:00:37.420 --> 00:00:42.160
We insert the screwdriver here and simply lever it out. 
